Introduction¶

In this project, I used datasets from Gapminder data world to analyze the countries performance in (Economy ,Health, and Social fields)¶
,i used 4 independent variables and 1 dependent variable to evaluate that performance. i will choose the last to decades (2000-2018) to analyze¶
1- independent variables :¶
  • Total population
  • Life expectancy
  • GDP per Capita (a country's economic output per person) GDP/Total population
  • Health per GDP (percentage of health expenditure to GDP) this data wasn't updated in gapminder so i get it from WHO data (https://apps.who.int/nha/database/Select/Indicators/en)
2-Dependent variable:¶
  • Happiness score
Questions i will answers from this analysis:¶
  • 1-which is the heighest continent performance in each indicator ?
  • 2- which are Top 10 performance countries in each indicator?
  • 3- which are Bottom 10 performance countries ?
  • 4- How is Egypt performance in each indicator over years?
  • 5- is there any correlation between indicators?
  • 6- by income level is there any changes in number of countries in each level ? or any increase in number of countries that gone from low to middel or high income?
  • 7- after spotting highest countries performance choose one to analyse it in details
  • 8- what is the indicator that have the bigest impact on happiness score?

# code to display dataframs side by side in jupyter (source: Stackoverflow ) 

from IPython.core.display import display, HTML

def display_side_by_side(dfs:list, captions:list):
    """Display tables side by side to save vertical space
    Input:
        dfs: list of pandas.DataFrame
        captions: list of table captions
    """
    output = ""
    combined = dict(zip(captions, dfs))
    for caption, df in combined.items():
        output += df.style.set_table_attributes("style='display:inline'").set_caption(caption)._repr_html_()
        output += "\xa0\xa0\xa0"
    display(HTML(output))

#it looks like there is a serious dirty data here i will extract data value from a string and converting it to int

pop_num=[]

for x in total_population2.total_population:
    if x[-1]=="M":
        x=x.replace("M","")
        f=float(x)
        pop_num.append(f*1000000)   
    elif x[-1]=="k":
        x=x.replace("k","")
        f=float(x)
        pop_num.append(f*1000)
    
    elif x[-1]=="B":
        x=x.replace("B","")
        f=float(x)
        pop_num.append(f*1000000000)
    else:
        f=float(x)
        pop_num.append(f)
        
total_population2["total_population"]=pop_num

Conclusions:¶

After analysizing this large data sets from gapminder world (in the 5 chosen indicators) :¶

  • we find that the GDP per capita has a strong positive correlation to happiness score, this only in GDP per capita below 60000, in GDP per capita above 60000 there is no correlation
  • also there is a positive correlation between happiness score and life expactancy
  • we also found that the people above 70 years old age are most benefits from government spend on health

Limitation of data :¶

  • There was alot of missing data specially in happiness score data and this affect on findings and building a clear correlations
  • also there is limitied data in some indicators like (health per GDP ) only data from 2000 to 2018 are available
